Use this one approach:

Sync ARM64 assets → move backend to ARM64 → test one ARM64 canary agent → move all agents to ARM64

Assume:

export NS=sensu
export ARGO_APP=sensu-stg
export BACKEND_NAME=sensu-backend
export AGENT_DS=sensu-agent
export SENSU_IMAGE="sensu/sensu:6.14.0"

Change names if yours are different.


---

1. Verify Graviton nodes exist

kubectl get nodes -L kubernetes.io/arch

You should see at least one node with:

arm64

Check only ARM64 nodes:

kubectl get nodes -l kubernetes.io/arch=arm64


---

2. Verify Sensu image supports ARM64

docker buildx imagetools inspect ${SENSU_IMAGE} | grep -E "linux/(amd64|arm64)"

Expected:

linux/amd64
linux/arm64


---

3. Sync your updated assets first

Since you already added both amd64 and arm64 asset builds, commit that first.

git status
git add .
git commit -m "Add arm64 builds for Sensu assets"
git push

Sync ArgoCD:

argocd app diff ${ARGO_APP}
argocd app sync ${ARGO_APP}
argocd app wait ${ARGO_APP} --sync --health --timeout 600

Verify Sensu sees both architectures:

sensuctl asset list --format yaml | grep -E "name:|amd64|arm64"


---

4. Move Sensu backend to ARM64

Create a Kustomize patch:

mkdir -p overlays/stg/patches
cat > overlays/stg/patches/sensu-backend-arm64.yaml <<'EOF'
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: StatefulSet
metadata:
  name: sensu-backend
spec:
  template:
    spec:
      nodeSelector:
        kubernetes.io/arch: arm64
      tolerations:
        - key: graviton
          operator: Equal
          value: "true"
          effect: NoSchedule
EOF

If your backend is a Deployment, change this line:

kind: StatefulSet

to:

kind: Deployment

Add patch to overlays/stg/kustomization.yaml:

cat >> overlays/stg/kustomization.yaml <<'EOF'

patches:
  - path: patches/sensu-backend-arm64.yaml
EOF

If your kustomization.yaml already has patches:, add only this line under it:

- path: patches/sensu-backend-arm64.yaml

Commit and sync:

git add overlays/stg
git commit -m "Move Sensu backend to arm64 in STG"
git push

argocd app sync ${ARGO_APP}
argocd app wait ${ARGO_APP} --sync --health --timeout 600

Validate:

kubectl get pods -n ${NS} -o wide | grep sensu-backend
kubectl logs -n ${NS} sts/${BACKEND_NAME} --tail=100
sensuctl entity list
sensuctl event list

If backend is a deployment:

kubectl logs -n ${NS} deploy/${BACKEND_NAME} --tail=100


---

5. Test one ARM64 canary agent

Label one ARM64 node:

ARM_NODE=$(kubectl get nodes -l kubernetes.io/arch=arm64 -o jsonpath='{.items[0].metadata.name}')
kubectl label node ${ARM_NODE} sensu-arm64-canary=true --overwrite

Create a canary patch by copying your existing agent DaemonSet YAML into a new manifest is safest. If you already have the agent manifest in Git, copy it:

cp base/sensu-agent.yaml overlays/stg/sensu-agent-arm64-canary.yaml

Edit the copied file:

vi overlays/stg/sensu-agent-arm64-canary.yaml

Change these fields:

metadata:
  name: sensu-agent-arm64-canary

spec:
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: sensu-agent-arm64-canary

  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: sensu-agent-arm64-canary
    spec:
      nodeSelector:
        kubernetes.io/arch: arm64
        sensu-arm64-canary: "true"
      tolerations:
        - key: graviton
          operator: Equal
          value: "true"
          effect: NoSchedule

Also make sure the canary agent has a separate subscription, for example:

stg-arm64-canary

Add the canary manifest to overlays/stg/kustomization.yaml:

resources:
  - sensu-agent-arm64-canary.yaml

Commit and sync:

git add overlays/stg
git commit -m "Add Sensu arm64 canary agent in STG"
git push

argocd app sync ${ARGO_APP}
argocd app wait ${ARGO_APP} --sync --health --timeout 600

Validate canary pod is on ARM64:

kubectl get pods -n ${NS} -o wide | grep sensu-agent-arm64-canary
kubectl get node ${ARM_NODE} -o jsonpath='{.metadata.labels.kubernetes\.io/arch}'; echo

Expected:

arm64

Check Sensu entity:

sensuctl entity list | grep arm64
sensuctl event list

Check logs:

kubectl logs -n ${NS} ds/sensu-agent-arm64-canary --tail=200

Look for these errors:

exec format error
no matching asset build
failed to fetch asset
ruby not found
permission denied


---

6. Move main Sensu agent DaemonSet to ARM64

Only after the canary works, create the main agent patch:

cat > overlays/stg/patches/sensu-agent-arm64.yaml <<'EOF'
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: DaemonSet
metadata:
  name: sensu-agent
spec:
  template:
    spec:
      nodeSelector:
        kubernetes.io/arch: arm64
      tolerations:
        - key: graviton
          operator: Equal
          value: "true"
          effect: NoSchedule
EOF

Add it to kustomization.yaml under patches:

- path: patches/sensu-agent-arm64.yaml

Commit and sync:

git add overlays/stg
git commit -m "Move Sensu agents to arm64 in STG"
git push

argocd app sync ${ARGO_APP}
argocd app wait ${ARGO_APP} --sync --health --timeout 600

Validate:

kubectl get pods -n ${NS} -o wide | grep sensu-agent
kubectl get nodes -L kubernetes.io/arch
sensuctl entity list
sensuctl event list
kubectl logs -n ${NS} ds/${AGENT_DS} --tail=200


---

7. After all agents are ARM64, remove canary

Remove the canary resource from kustomization.yaml, delete the canary file, then commit:

git rm overlays/stg/sensu-agent-arm64-canary.yaml
git add overlays/stg/kustomization.yaml
git commit -m "Remove Sensu arm64 canary agent"
git push

argocd app sync ${ARGO_APP}
argocd app wait ${ARGO_APP} --sync --health --timeout 600

Remove node label:

kubectl label node ${ARM_NODE} sensu-arm64-canary-

Final check:

kubectl get pods -n ${NS} -o wide
sensuctl event list
sensuctl entity list

This gives you one clean path: assets first, backend ARM64, canary agent ARM64, then all agents ARM64.